      • setLogSer

        public static boolean setLogSer(java.lang.String url)
        register the log data server. this method first get a reference of remote object using String url then it calls aya method. if the the object reference is successfully obtain then it will update log and return true. if any exception occur while the getting reference of remote object then this method returns false without updating reference.
        Note :- if the new remote server is added then the old one is removed if any.(reference of log server is maintained internally)
        Parameters:
        url - URI of remote data Server.
        Returns:
        true if successfully updated, false if not updated due to some reason.

      • registerDataSer

        public static boolean registerDataSer(java.lang.String url)
        register the data server. this method first get a reference of remote object using String url then it calls aya method. if the the object reference is successfully obtain then it will add in the dataSer and return true. if any exception occur while the getting reference of remote object then this method returns false without updating reference.
        Note :- if the new remote server is added then the old one is not removed if any.(list of data server is maintained internally)
        Parameters:
        url - URI of remote data Server.
        Returns:
        true if successfully added, false if not added due to some reason.
